The paper deals with maximizing the sum rate in interference-limited scenarios in wireless networks, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm involves adjusting transmit and receive filters, which is a signal processing technique (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of relays in the network, which falls under the category of wireless communication (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to formulate the optimization problem, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG) who work on developing new optimization techniques.
